-- European Coal for Next Year Declines for Fourth Straight Day
-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r o w n
-- 2012-12-07T10:35:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-06/european-coal-for-next-year-declines-to-lowest-level-in-week.html
European coal for 2013 delivery
dropped for a fourth consecutive day.  Thermal coal for delivery next year to Amsterdam, Rotterdam
or Antwerp declined as much as 40 cents, or 0.4 percent, to
$95.50 a metric ton, the lowest level since Nov. 28, according
to data compiled by Bloomberg. It was at $95.65 at 10:22 a.m.
London time.  Bloomberg tracks information from ICAP Plc, GFI Group Inc.,
Marex Spectron Group Ltd., Credit Suisse Group AG, IHS
McCloskey, Tradition Financial Services and Tullett Prebon Plc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
